    {
      "id": "609c63d4a4d7c054c3843ad9eff482766bef91f7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-12 09:22:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nMaybe I'm missing something, but we definitely used to have interfaces of this type, such as qswlnd and gmlnd, that has numeric interface names. Rathe rhan hard-code the string-to-nid conversion, each LND type registered its own NID parsing method that was used. That allowed arbitrary parsing routines if needed, but allowed shared routines for the common IPv4 dotted-quad format.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2073ba346435c15af236fc1175063674e136cf8c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-12 09:31:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI asked:\n> “Should this get a tag:\n> Fixes: ce873599 (\"LU-8769 lnet: removal of obsolete LNDs\")\n> or was there an earlier patch that broke this?  Definitely qswlnd\n>  previously had numeric NIDs, and I think gmlnd also.”\n \nTo which Grégoire replied:\n> I think the dynamic lnet configuration was not already\n> supported at the time the previous numeric NIDs LNDs\n> was in use. That’s why I did not mention any related patch.\n\nOK, that avoids th need for the Fixes: tag, but still makes me wonder if there is a need for more abstraction here?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3bc60ef05b1947404d68014660af68871e55825e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-12 20:44:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "75ce02da06464fc0ab28edf2d2383082d16e1f3d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-12 21:15:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAs far as I understand, there is no exported generic routine that parses the address part of a nid. Currently only libcfs_str2net() and libcfs_str2nid() routines are non static.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "5cd6e6cdfac3b158a072a1ba665222ff9d3dfd07",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 549,
        "name": "Misc Code Checks Robot (Gatekeeper helper)",
        "username": "smatchreview",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
